      "content": "```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"toolu_019T7MKsvx1G5MwqUPGvKWt1\",\n  \"name\": \"filesystem\",\n  \"content\": \"# AIFPL Pending Improvements\\n\\nThis document records the remaining issues identified in the AIFPL language design\\nreview, for follow-up in a future session.\\n\\nSome items were completed previously and are no longer in this list.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \\ud83d\\udd35 Omissions Worth Considering\\n\\nThese are lower priority \\u2014 useful but not blocking anything.\\n\\n**#19 \\u2014 No `alist-map` / `alist-filter`**\\n\\nWorking with alist values requires extracting keys/values as lists, processing them,\\nand reconstructing. There are no higher-order operations that work directly on alist\\nentries as `(key, value)` pairs. These could be implemented as prelude lambdas.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**#20 \\u2014 No `string-split` (filter empty parts)**\\n\\n`string->list` with a delimiter splits on every occurrence, producing empty strings\\nfor consecutive delimiters. A `string-split` that filters empty parts is common for\\nwhitespace-separated data.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**#23 \\u2014 No `list-sort` / `list-sort-by`**\\n\\nNo built-in sorting. Implementing merge sort in AIFPL is possible but expensive for\\nan AI tool where conciseness matters. Would require a comparison function argument.\\n\",\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```\n`content` is:\n```markdown\n# AIFPL Pending Improvements\n\nThis document records the remaining issues identified in the AIFPL language design\nreview, for follow-up in a future session.\n\nSome items were completed previously and are no longer in this list.\n\n---\n\n### \ud83d\udd35 Omissions Worth Considering\n\nThese are lower priority \u2014 useful but not blocking anything.\n\n**#19 \u2014 No `alist-map` / `alist-filter`**\n\nWorking with alist values requires extracting keys/values as lists, processing them,\nand reconstructing. There are no higher-order operations that work directly on alist\nentries as `(key, value)` pairs. These could be implemented as prelude lambdas.\n\n---\n\n**#20 \u2014 No `string-split` (filter empty parts)**\n\n`string->list` with a delimiter splits on every occurrence, producing empty strings\nfor consecutive delimiters. A `string-split` that filters empty parts is common for\nwhitespace-separated data.\n\n---\n\n**#23 \u2014 No `list-sort` / `list-sort-by`**\n\nNo built-in sorting. Implementing merge sort in AIFPL is possible but expensive for\nan AI tool where conciseness matters. Would require a comparison function argument.\n\n```",
