      "type": "user_message",
      "content": "something else. Right now it feels slightly odd that we have this specialized class of list/dictionary but I can imagine that in the future we might need other specialized types too.\n\nIgnore how alists are implemented now, if we wanted to use the underlying list type, what other capabilities would we need to allow O(1) operations on some new implementation but where the base operations were done on regular lists? Is this even possible?",
