    {
      "id": "52af8569-e4a6-48f3-b0f9-3b2bd72e72e5",
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T06:27:15.451019+00:00",
      "type": "user_message",
      "content": "this is more about what will be the best way to implement more structured data in a natural and high-performance way. The current implementation is immtuable but actually the immutability guarantee we really want is whether something appears to be immutable to the user. If, say, the user's request could best be implemented via a mutation because the mutated value will never be reused then that's much more efficient computationally. I'm planning for that future",
