    {
      "id": "77a60ebe-efdf-4ba3-9599-df09b1b7a3fa",
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T06:36:28.578474+00:00",
      "type": "user_message",
      "content": "ok - so let's think about this from a practical perspective. We're currently using \"alist\" but we don't actually quite have normal alist semantics - we're actually a \"dict\".\n\nMy primary concerns are to be able to implement a high performance object-like system, or at least something that allows for more structured records. These might more naturally be dictionaries than lists?",
